    dc:creator "Smid, Jiri; Fernandez, Sergio Matilla; Elmi, Hassan Sh Abdirahman; Mazuch, Tomas" ;
    dc:title "Psammophis cornusafricae Šmíd & Fernández & Elmi & Mazuch 2023, sp. nov." ;
    dwc:basisOfRecord <http://tb.plazi.org/GgServer/dwcaRecords/AC163C4651DB5A75B010474138FFA177.mc.11184D65061F3030A34243C1C5685F6F> ;
    trt:definesTaxonConcept <http://taxon-concept.plazi.org/id/Animalia/Psammophis_cornusafricae_%C5%A0m%C3%ADd_2023> ;
    trt:publishedIn <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.99.101943> ;
    a trt:Treatment .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.99.101943>
    bibo:endPage "361" ;
    bibo:issue "2" ;
    bibo:journal "Zoosystematics and Evolution" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-06-27" ;
    bibo:startPage "345" ;
    bibo:volume "99" ;
    dc:creator "Smid, Jiri; Fernandez, Sergio Matilla; Elmi, Hassan Sh Abdirahman; Mazuch, Tomas" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Diversity of Sand Snakes (Psammophiidae, Psammophis) in the Horn of Africa, with the description of a new species from Somalia" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.99.101943.figure6>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.99.101943.figure7>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.99.101943.figure4>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.99.101943.figure8> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.99.101943.figure6>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Holotype of Psammophis cornusafricae sp. nov. (MVZ: Herp: 242772)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/869481" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.99.101943.figure7>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Psammophis cornusafricae sp. nov. in life (specimen NMP-P 6 V 76373, sample JIR 510), with a close-up of the head in the upper left corner, and the habitat at the locality where the specimen was found (8.5 km S of Yuffleh, Somaliland) at the bottom." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/869482" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.99.101943.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Maximum Likelihood phylogeny of the genus Psammophis based on a concatenated alignment of the cyt b, ND 4 and c-mos genes (2,149 bp in total). The clade containing P. biseriatus, P. tanganicus and P. cornusafricae sp. nov. is highlighted in pink. Codes of samples newly sequenced for this study are in red. Locality details and original references of all samples are given in Suppl. material 1. Branch support is given in the order SH-aLRT / UFBoot / Standard bootstrap / MrBayes posterior probability." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/869479" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.99.101943.figure8>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Distribution of P. biseriatus, P. tanganicus and P. cornusafricae sp. nov. in the Horn of Africa. Localities sampled for the genetic analysis are shown along with sample codes. The background layer shows shaded relief and water bodies and drainages and was made with Natural Earth (www. naturalearthdata. com). The species range maps were derived from Roll et al. (2017, 2021), Spawls et al. (2023), and the findings presented in this study." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/869483" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

